race.comment: NARAGHI (10) improved sharply beaten 2L at Geelong and there was plenty of merit in the effort. Has the tongue tie applied for the first time and will present at peak. A solid each-way chance. WHITE HOT MAMA (11) looked a run short at Tatura on debut and has been kept on the fresh side. Has an awkward gate but Jamie Melham's booking suggests she's pleasing and a sharper run is on the cards. M'LADY ROSE (9) debuts for the local McEvoy yard and placed second at Flemington in her most recent jumpout. The yard gets them going early and Currie rides. She'll also need a touch of luck from the gate.
